  "prompt": "Do airplanes float on water?",
  "response": "Airplanes are not designed to float on water like boats. However, some aircraft, particularly those known as seaplanes or amphibious planes, are built with special features that enable them to land on and take off from water.\n\nIn emergency situations, such as a forced water landing, larger commercial airplanes like jets are equipped with certain buoyant features, including inflatable life rafts and life vests, to help passengers evacuate safely. These planes can stay afloat for a limited period, allowing evacuation procedures to be carried out.\n\nThe capacity of an airplane to stay afloat depends on various factors like the type of airplane, the condition of the water landing, and any damage the airplane might have incurred. Ultimately, while standard commercial airliners are not built to float for extended periods, they are designed to provide enough buoyancy for emergency situations and passenger evacuation.",
